      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 2007: loadMissingBodyOverwrites() only records a message as processed when the plugin returns a non-empty or explicitly empty bodyOverwrite. If a handler leaves pluginData untouched for messages it does not transform, those messages remain missing the key and will be reprocessed on every loadMissingBodyOverwrites() call, causing repeated plugin work and repeated latency after each load. Mark absent results as processed as well, or make the handler contract require an explicit empty value and enforce that in ChatServicesManager. Suggested fix:\\n```suggestion\\nconst auto boIt \u003d transformed.pluginData.find(\\\"bodyOverwrite\\\");\\nconst auto overwrite \u003d boIt \u003d\u003d transformed.pluginData.end() ? std::string {} : boIt-\u003esecond;\\nif (auto signalMsg \u003d injectEditionOverwrites(transformed.id, overwrite);\\n    !signalMsg.id.empty() \u0026\u0026 !overwrite.empty()) {\\n    signalMap[signalMsg.id] \u003d std::move(signalMsg);\\n}\\n```",
